To account for the latency associated with the effects of temperature, new and historical incidences, and human interaction on the spread of COVID-19, we generated four temporal weekly lags of features in categories B–E (we assume that the features in category A are static during our study period). Notably, for category C, we also included (natural log-transformed values of) change in cumulative incidence rate (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
