While SCI provides a measure of connectivity, our goal is to capture the spatiotemporal lags of COVID-19 cases in county i, i.e., the number of recent COVID-19 cases in other counties connected to county i. Using SCI, Kuchler et al.6 created a new metric, called Social Proximity to Cases (SPC) for each county, which is a measure of the level of exposure to COVID-19 cases in connected counties through social connectedness. We use a slight variation of SPC, defined as follows for county i at time t:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
